article.headline: Jacksonville 78, North Florida 73
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Antonio Cool scored 21 points and Haminn Quaintance added 16 to lead Jacksonville University to a 78-73 win over North Florida on Tuesday night. The Dolphins (1-1) appeared to be headed for a comfortable win, holding a 10-point lead at 73-63 with less than 4 minutes left in the game. But North Florida (1-4) went on an 8-1 run in the next 3 minutes, cutting the margin to 74-71 on Derrick Scott's reverse lay-up with less than 1 minute to play. That was as close as the Ospreys would get. Jacksonville guard David Lee converted two free throw attempts with 31 seconds remaining and Cool added two more with 18 seconds left to offset Riley Didion's lay-up in the closing seconds. Cool scored 11 of his game-high 21 points in the first half while Quaintance paced the Dolphins' second half attack with nine points in the final 20 minutes. Jacksonville led 40-36 at halftime and doubled that margin in the first four minutes of the second half. The Dolphins' biggest lead came at the 8:07 mark when Quaintance's lay-up gave Jacksonville a 65-54 advantage. Three other Dolphins scored in double figures. North Florida also had a balanced attack with Chris Timberlake's 16 points leading five North Florida players in double figures. Division II North Florida is in the process of becoming a Division I member and will join Jacksonville in the Atlantic Sun Conference next year.
